# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# BHC — environment variables (template)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Copy this file to .env.local and fill in the values. .env.local is
# gitignored and never committed. Mirror these into Vercel before
# deploying anything that depends on them.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ─── Neon Postgres ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
# DATABASE_URL: pooled connection (host contains "-pooler") — used by
#   runtime queries from Next.js routes + server components on Vercel.
# DATABASE_URL_UNPOOLED: direct connection (no -pooler) — used by
#   Drizzle Kit migrations. PgBouncer doesn't support all the session
#   commands a migration runner needs.
# Find both strings in the Neon dashboard → Connection Details.
DATABASE_URL=
DATABASE_URL_UNPOOLED=

# ─── Phase 2A: nothing else needed ───────────────────────────────────
# Phase 2B (Stripe, Resend, Loops, Cloudflare Stream, R2) will add:
#   STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=
#   STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET=
#   RESEND_API_KEY=
#   LOOPS_API_KEY=
#   CLOUDFLARE_ACCOUNT_ID=
#   CLOUDFLARE_STREAM_TOKEN=
#   CLOUDFLARE_R2_ACCESS_KEY_ID=
#   CLOUDFLARE_R2_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=
#   CLOUDFLARE_R2_BUCKET=
#   NEXT_PUBLIC_GA_ID=
#   NEXT_PUBLIC_POSTHOG_KEY=
#   NEXT_PUBLIC_POSTHOG_HOST=
#   SESSION_SECRET=
